        "text_FHUGRh": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>1. Get a family member or friend to help take your measurements.</p><p>2. Use a soft measuring tape and don’t pull too tight or too loose – It should be taut not cutting.</p><p>3. Your hip measurement is taken at the widest part of the lower body, including the curve of the bottom. It is not taken at the hip bones.</p><p>4. Take into account any undergarments.</p><p>5. We appreciate that everybody has a unique shape, so the sizing guide will help you find the closest fit for you, though it is most likely that some additional alterations may be required for a perfect, tailored fit.</p>",
            "width": "100%",
            "max_width": "normal",
            "alignment": "center",
            "type_preset": "rte",
            "enable_mobile_size": false,
            "mobile_font_size": "1rem",
